results.text: I was born in Philadelphia in 1979, grew up in inner city. My mother raised two boys by herself. My father was in and out of my childhood. It's Kevin getting his act together. He wants you all to see how he's dance. Of course, we struggle financially, but my mom did a great job being a parent. I credit my mom for giving me the understanding of hard work, dedication. What you put into something is what you get out of it.

I did my first stand up show in 1998. Our first big break was just the last comedy festival. That comedy performance was watched by agents, execs managers. My acting career got to be explosive because of an amazing producer named Will Packer. He gave me an opportunity to start a movie called Sank Like a man. And that movie was set up for me to knock the ball out of the park. I've had ten number one films.

Those films have surpassed $4.2 billion in the box office, and I am now the highest paid comedian in the world. Stardom is amazing, but I quickly realized that stardom only gets you so far. I started Harvey Productions because I didn't want to be the star that was just to work for hire. Starting a production company meant that I could actually be a part of the creative. That's when the business mind kind of kicked into overdrive.

We produce television, movies, develop and sell original IP. There's a literature entity. The goal was to have something that acts as a complete circle that services everything in it. Then there's another world. The world adventure, the VC world. So I decided to create Heartbeat Ventures. It's all about financial inclusion. These are doors that were closed for quite some time, especially to my culture. We have about 35 companies that we've invested in.

Athletics, beyond meat, their body liquid, IV, ate sleep. We've managed to put ourselves in position to be a real player in this state. So many people feel like you have a cap of opportunity in life. I don't look at it that way. I look at it as life presents you with so many doors, you just have the choice to turn them off and open them.

Where I come from, the little kids that look like me, we're not expected to make it. We're not expected to see the higher levels of life. It's a fact. My story does a lot more for those kids than people may think. To show that the dream is real, to say, hey, I came from the same place. I put my head down. I worked. I got opportunities. I made the best out of them.

But it's possible for us all if we truly believe so as Heartbeat Ventures grows, you'll see a real initiative in closing that big financial gap between my culture and mainstream America. My success is going to ultimately help close the gap.
